{"nodes": [{"id": "2026_06_09_add_action_keybinding_presets_design_document", "label": "Design", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-add-action-keybinding-presets/design.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_09_add_action_keybinding_presets_design_context", "label": "Context", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-add-action-keybinding-presets/design.md", "source_location": "line 1", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "`piVimMode.keymap.actions` already supports finite bindable prompt transform actions, and `src/action-keybinding-recipes.ts` already owns source-backed copy-pasteable recipes for paragraph editing and Markdown wrapping. The remaining friction is configuration ergonomics: users must paste nested JSON snippets instead of selecting a named bundle. This change adds a small config-resolution layer. It must not alter prompt transform semantics, modal dispatch, registers, marks, dot-repeat, search high"}, {"id": "2026_06_09_add_action_keybinding_presets_design_goals_non_goals", "label": "Goals / Non-Goals", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-add-action-keybinding-presets/design.md", "source_location": "line 7", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "**Goals:** - Add `piVimMode.keymap.actionPresets` as an opt-in array of named built-in action keybinding presets."}, {"id": "2026_06_09_add_action_keybinding_presets_design_decisions", "label": "Decisions", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-add-action-keybinding-presets/design.md", "source_location": "line 25", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "1. **Use `piVimMode.keymap.actionPresets` under keymap.** - Target seams: `src/types.ts`, `src/config.ts`, `docs/settings.md`, `openspec/specs/vim-keymap-configuration/spec.md`. - Decision: accept an array of finite preset IDs such as `[\"paragraph-editing\", \"markdown-wrapping\"]`; default is absent/empty."}, {"id": "2026_06_09_add_action_keybinding_presets_design_risks_trade_offs", "label": "Risks / Trade-offs", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-add-action-keybinding-presets/design.md", "source_location": "line 63", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "- **Preset vs recipe terminology confusion** \u2192 Docs distinguish recipes as copy-paste snippets and presets as config-selected bundles backed by the same metadata. - **Unexpected overrides when combining presets** \u2192 Define listed-order merge semantics and test overlapping `quote`/`unquote` bindings. - **Preset bindings rejected by disabled transforms or future grammar changes** \u2192 Reuse existing resolver and add tests proving warnings occur while valid siblings survive."}, {"id": "2026_06_09_add_action_keybinding_presets_design_migration_plan", "label": "Migration Plan", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-add-action-keybinding-presets/design.md", "source_location": "line 72", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "1. Add typed preset ID metadata by reusing or renaming the recipe registry. 2. Extend config parsing for `piVimMode.keymap.actionPresets` with field-by-field warnings for unsupported values and non-array input. 3. Expand preset actions before explicit `keymap.actions` at global/project layers."}, {"id": "2026_06_09_add_action_keybinding_presets_design_open_questions", "label": "Open Questions", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-add-action-keybinding-presets/design.md", "source_location": "line 84", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "- Should the implementation keep the existing `ACTION_KEYBINDING_RECIPES` export name and add preset aliases, or rename the module to presets with recipe compatibility exports? - Decision: `markdown-wrapping` uses `gT` with no default language specifier; users can override `prompt.transform.fence` explicitly when they want a language like `ts`. - Should runtime help show a minimal JSON fragment for `actionPresets`, or only list preset IDs and point to settings docs?"}, {"id": "2026_06_09_add_action_keybinding_presets_design_ref_src_action_keybinding_recipes_ts", "label": "action-keybinding-recipes.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-add-action-keybinding-presets/design.md", "source_location": "line 3", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_09_add_action_keybinding_presets_design_ref_src_types_ts", "label": "types.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-add-action-keybinding-presets/design.md", "source_location": "line 28", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_09_add_action_keybinding_presets_design_ref_src_config_ts", "label": "config.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-add-action-keybinding-presets/design.md", "source_location": "line 28", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_09_add_action_keybinding_presets_design_ref_docs_settings_md", "label": "settings.md", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-add-action-keybinding-presets/design.md", "source_location": "line 28", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_09_add_action_keybinding_presets_design_ref_openspec_specs_vim_keymap_configuration_spec_md", "label": "spec.md", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-add-action-keybinding-presets/design.md", "source_location": "line 28", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}], "edges": [{"source": "2026_06_09_add_action_keybinding_presets_design_document", "target": "2026_06_09_add_action_keybinding_presets_design_context", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-add-action-keybinding-presets/design.md", "source_location": "line 1", "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "2026_06_09_add_action_keybinding_presets_design_document", "target": "2026_06_09_add_action_keybinding_presets_design_goals_non_goals", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-add-action-keybinding-presets/design.md", "source_location": "line 7", "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "2026_06_09_add_action_keybinding_presets_design_document", "target": "2026_06_09_add_action_keybinding_presets_design_decisions", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-add-action-keybinding-presets/design.md", "source_location": "line 25", "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "2026_06_09_add_action_keybinding_presets_design_document", "target": "2026_06_09_add_action_keybinding_presets_design_risks_trade_offs", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-add-action-keybinding-presets/design.md", "source_location": "line 63", "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "2026_06_09_add_action_keybinding_presets_design_document", "target": "2026_06_09_add_action_keybinding_presets_design_migration_plan", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-09-add-action-ke